File and Directory Management
-----------------------------
ls                        List directory contents
cd                        Change directory
pwd                       Print working directory
mkdir                     Create a new directory
rm                        Remove files or directories
cp                        Copy files or directories
mv                        Move or rename files or directories
touch                     Create an empty file
find                      Search for files and directories
stat                      Display detailed info about a file

File Viewing and Editing
------------------------
cat                       View file contents (short files)
less / more               View file contents page by page
head / tail               View the beginning/end of files
nano / vim                Text editors (nano = simpler, vim = powerful)

Searching and Filtering
-----------------------
grep                      Search for patterns in files
awk                       Pattern scanning and processing
sed                       Stream editor for filtering and transforming text
cut                       Remove sections from each line of input
sort                      Sort lines in text files
uniq                      Remove duplicate lines

System Information
------------------
top / htop                Real-time system resource monitor
free -h                   Show memory usage
df -h                     Disk space usage
du -sh                    Directory size summary
uname -a                  System info
uptime                    System running time and load
whoami                    Display current user
id                        Show user ID and groups

User and Permissions
--------------------
chmod                     Change file permissions
chown                     Change file ownership
adduser / useradd         Add a new user
passwd                    Set/change password
su / sudo                 Switch user or run as root

Networking
----------
ip a                      Show IP addresses
ping                      Check network connectivity
curl                      Transfer data from or to a server
wget                      Download files from the internet
netstat / ss              Show network sockets and ports
traceroute                Trace the route to a host
nslookup / dig            DNS query tools

Package Management
------------------
apt                       Debian/Ubuntu: install/update packages
yum / dnf                 RedHat/CentOS: install/update packages
pacman                    Arch: install/update packages

Process and Service Management
------------------------------
ps aux                    List running processes
kill / killall            Terminate a process
systemctl                 Manage systemd services
service                   Start/stop services (older systems)

Archive and Compression
-----------------------
tar -czf / -xzf           Create/extract tar.gz archives
zip / unzip               Zip and unzip files
gzip / gunzip             Compress and decompress files

